description.narrative: The key objective of the project is to: Improve mobility in areas of participating metropolitan, municipal or district assemblies (MMDAs) through a combination of traffic engineering measures, management improvements, regulation of the public transport industry, and implementation of a Bus Rapid Transit (BRT) system.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :2.02 (a) | Description :CUT will be established and will assume all functions of the PAO | Due Date :01-Jan-2010

Finance Agreement :2.05 (a) | Description :A UPTU will be established in each participating Accra MMDA and each Kumasi MMDA andthereafter maintained at all times during theimplementation of the project. | Due Date :31-Dec-2008

Finance Agreement :2.05 (a) | Description :A UPTU will be established in each participating Accra MMDA and each Kumasi MMDA andthereafter maintained at all times during theimplementation of the project. | Due Date :31-Dec-2009

Finance Agreement :2.06 (b) | Description :GOG to provide financing for consultants' services and operating costs for PAO and CUT,contributing 25% during first year, 50% second year, 75% third year, 100% thereafter | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :2.B (3) | Description :GOG will provide to the Association annual audit reports by June 30 of each year for thepreceding FY. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :2.C (1) | Description :Each year, GOG will prepare and submit to IDA an Annual Work Plan | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :2.D (1) | Description :GOG to prepare and disclose a RAP, EIA AND EMP in accordance with RPF and ESMF, carry outall required measures under the RAP and EMP to be implemented before commencing any civil works under project. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :4.02 | Description :If AFD co-financing fails to become effective by March 31, 2008, IDA reserves the right tosuspend all or part of the IDA/GEF funding. | Due Date :31-Mar-2008
